Introduction

Kim Sun-woo is a South Korean singer, rapper, and songwriter under ONE HUNDRED. As a trainee, he participated in the 2017 reality show 'High School Rapper.' He made his official debut on December 6, 2017, as the main rapper of the boy group "The Boyz."
